        <p class="metadata">Posted by Darby Felton (darby) on 2008-04-01T13:37:27.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>The HtmlEntities filter uses <a href="http://php.net/htmlentities">htmlentities()</a>, which the manual describes as having a {{$charset}} option, hence its {{(get|set)CharSet()}} method naming.</p>

<p>The StringToLower and StringToUpper filters use <a href="http://php.net/mb_strtolower">mb_strtolower</a> and <a href="http://php.net/mb_strtoupper">mb_strtoupper</a>, respectively, each of which has an {{$encoding}} option.</p>

<p>Thus, the consistency lies with the naming of the arguments of PHP functions used in the filters.</p>

<p>I suppose this could be changed, but which way is better, or what other way would be even better yet?</p>

<p>In any case, the old method names would not be able to be removed any time soon in the interest of backward compatibility.</p>

